Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about language models and natural language processing tasks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the benefits of model size and proposes a model-parallel algorithm for training language models. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper deals with model parallelism and training large models that require distributed computing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the performance of language models in various NLP tasks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper deals with training neural language models and proposes a new algorithm for model parallelism.
